sentence: After Nas blamed Southern hip hop as the cause of the perceived artistic decline of the genre on his 2006 single Hip Hop Is Dead, from the Hip Hop Is Dead, his then- Def Jam labelmate Young Jeezy took offense by claiming that Nas had no street credibility and vowing his album The Inspiration would outsell Hip Hop is Dead, which were released one week apart from each other in December 2006.
